# space.word — what a SPACE is, has, and can. A place, where things stand.
# Bottoms out in the host (seed/materials/space/, the fold, schema, and locks). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, fold.word, name.word, being.word. `matter`, `type`, and
# `qualities` ground in the noun cluster alongside. The place root and heaven are the I_AM's.
# A space has a name, its label among siblings, never a Name. Its owner is a being (a beingId).

A space is a place, the fold of its fact chain.
A space is where a thing can be. Without a space, nothing has a where.
A space has a name, unique among the spaces beside it.
A space has a parent, the space it is under, and a point in it.
A space has a type, or none.
A space has a size, or none.
A space has an owner, a being, or none.
A space has qualities.
A space has children, the spaces, matter, and beings within it.
A space's owner can do on it, and on all under it.
A space with no owner has the owner of its parent.
The first space is the place root. Every space is under it, save the root itself.
A heaven space is the I_AM's own room.
A space can be born, under a parent or as a root.
A space can be named, given a type, and given an owner.
A space can be moved, to a new parent or point.
A space can die, set apart from its parent.
